------------------------------------------------------------
Caller: Paul Kavanagh, Solicitor for Henderson Insurance

Subject: Clarification of Liability for Incident Involving Dog

Executive Summary:
This call was about clarifying liability for an incident involving a dog that bit someone. Paul Kavanagh, solicitor for Henderson Insurance, called to discuss a letter received from Pemberton Insurance regarding one of their policyholders, Mr and Mrs Derek and Susan Farrell. The incident occurred on October 3rd, 2024, and involved their dog being walked by a neighbour, Mr Brian Nolan. Niamh O'Sullivan from Pemberton Insurance sought to determine if there was any dual insurance situation or how liability might be apportioned.

- The Farrells have a household policy with Henderson Insurance that includes personal liability cover.
- The dog was in Mr Nolan's care and control at the time of the incident.

Next Steps:
Pemberton Insurance: Send a letter to Henderson Insurance confirming the details discussed and requesting written confirmation of the Farrells' liability position.

Other: Henderson Insurance will send a letter confirming they are on risk and investigating, but will need to speak to the Farrells first.
