Caller: Paul Kavanagh, Insurance Company Representative (Henderson Insurance)

Subject: Clarification on Liability and Insurance Position for Incident PI-2024-71123

Executive Summary:
The call was about clarifying the insurance position for an incident involving a dog bite. Paul Kavanagh from Henderson Insurance called to discuss the liability and insurance coverage for the Farrells' dog, which was being walked by Mr. Brian Nolan at the time of the incident. Niamh O'Sullivan from Pemberton Insurance tried to determine if there was any dual insurance situation and how liability might be apportioned. The Farrells have liability cover with Henderson Insurance, but the company will need to take instructions from them on how to proceed.

- Incident date: 3rd of October 2024
- Policy reference: PI-2024-71123
- Farrells have liability cover with Henderson Insurance

Next Steps:
Pemberton Insurance: Request confirmation in writing from Henderson Insurance regarding their investigation and insurance position.
Other: Henderson Insurance will send a letter confirming they are on risk and investigating, but will need to speak to the Farrells first.

Liability Summary:
The Farrells may have some liability that attaches regardless of who was walking the dog at the time, as they are the dog owners. Henderson Insurance will need to take instructions from them on how to proceed.

Negotiation Summary:
Not applicable.

Vehicle Damage:
None.

Injury:
Not applicable.

Property:
Not applicable.
